{#
  Reusable "Latest analysis" rail — the section rendered on tool pages,
  sanctions tracker, calendar, travel, and sector pages that funnels
  crawl + reader traffic into the individual /briefing/<slug> analyses.

  Why this partial exists:
    Per-page bespoke briefing rails were drifting in style. Worse, each
    page had to re-implement the markup to surface a short list of
    recent briefings. The 2026-04 indexing audit flagged that briefings
    had inbound links only from /briefing (the chronological index,
    which Google deprioritises as it ages), so we want every steady-
    traffic page (tools, sanctions tracker, sector pages) to feed crawl
    signal into the briefings.

  Why the visual style changed in 2026-04:
    The original rail was a <ul> of title + date rows. The 2026-04 UX
    audit (alongside the drift in other internal-link sections) pushed
    every "related pages" block on the site onto the same 3-card grid
    pattern first shipped on /research/sdn/. This partial now delegates
    to templates/_card_grid.html.j2 so the rail matches every other
    discovery section on the site — readers see the same visual
    language everywhere, and we have one place to evolve the design.

  Inputs:
    recent_briefings : list of BlogPost rows with .slug, .title,
                       .published_date, optional .summary, .primary_sector,
                       .reading_minutes
    heading          : section heading; defaults to "Latest analysis"
    intro            : optional short paragraph above the grid

  Render no-ops if recent_briefings is empty so callers can pass it
  unconditionally.
#}
{% from "_card_grid.html.j2" import card_grid_section %}

{% macro recent_briefings_rail(recent_briefings, heading="Latest analysis", intro=None) -%}
{%- if recent_briefings %}
{%- set cards = [] %}
{%- for r in recent_briefings %}
{%-   set _eyebrow = (r.primary_sector|replace('_',' ')|upper) if r.primary_sector else 'ANALYSIS' %}
{%-   set _tagline = r.summary if r.summary else '' %}
{%-   set _meta_rows = [] %}
{%-   if r.published_date %}{%- set _ = _meta_rows.append('<strong>' ~ r.published_date.strftime('%b %d, %Y') ~ '</strong>') %}{%- endif %}
{%-   if r.reading_minutes %}{%- set _ = _meta_rows.append(r.reading_minutes|string ~ ' min read') %}{%- endif %}
{%-   set _ = cards.append({
        'href': '/briefing/' ~ r.slug,
        'eyebrow': _eyebrow,
        'title': r.title,
        'tagline': _tagline,
        'meta_rows': _meta_rows,
        'cta': 'Read analysis'
      }) %}
{%- endfor %}
{{ card_grid_section(
     heading=heading,
     intro=intro,
     cards=cards,
     aria_label=heading,
     footer_link={'href': '/briefing', 'label': 'Browse all daily briefings'},
     footer_mode='always'
) }}
{%- endif %}
{%- endmacro %}
